From f3ff723feb5c12f853b74484a573a43a075a942a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Date: Thu, 11 Jan 2018 11:08:37 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] staging: vc04_services: bcm2835-audio: remove redundant license text
Git-commit: f3ff723feb5c12f853b74484a573a43a075a942a
Patch-mainline: v4.16-rc1
References: FATE#324827

Now that the SPDX tag is in all
drivers/staging/vc04_services/bcm2835-audio/ files, that identifies the
license in a specific and legally-defined manner.  So the extra GPL text
wording can be removed as it is no longer needed at all.

This is done on a quest to remove the 700+ different ways that files in
the kernel describe the GPL license text.  And there's unneeded stuff
like the address (sometimes incorrect) for the FSF which is never
needed.

No copyright headers or other non-license-description text was removed.

